We are using angular js version 1 for our application.
So, I just wanted to try to perform the xss attack on our application using expressions.
The thing is in Angular JS the expressions within the double {{}} will not be executed directly by the javascript.
The input inside will go into the sandbox and as a result it wont execute.
So, now I tried to break out of the sandbox.
$on - This is the built in function for every scope
.constructor - For every function in the javascript there is a constructor property and it will return the base function.
('alert(1)'): Using base function constructor creating one new function.
(): Created function will be executed immediately.
{{}$on.constructor('alert(1)')()}

I have tried the same thing on our bank application.
But, everywhere in our application we have tied the input fields to the ng-modal.
In ng-model the data will only be stored but not evaluate the expressions. It will escape the expressions.
If we want it to execute in the application, this input directly needs to be evaluated in the html template
or we can directly store it in {{}} from the ng-model.
So, the attack was not successfull, but learnt the reasons behind it.
